full_text: Enough is enough. To those who are still hanging out with friends or hosting dinner parties: Do the right thing and stay home. And while you‚Äôre at home, share this video to remind others they need to stay home too. #PlankTheCurve https://t.co/b2q1fT81cO

We‚Äôre doing everything we can together to protect the health and safety of Canadians right across the country. Yesterday, @cafreeland and I spoke with premiers again about our cooperation to support everyone affected by COVID-19 and its impacts. More here: https://t.co/PqlJP2Qmq7
Let me be very clear: If you‚Äôve just returned from abroad, you must stay home and self-isolate for 14 days. This is not a suggestion. #StayAtHomeSaveLives

The legislation will be tabled without clause 2.

You need to stay home. And so do your friends and family members. Help spread the word with your own video - and tag your friends to remind them to stay home too. And together, we can #PlankTheCurve. @MichaelBuble and @VancityReynolds - can you help? #StayAtHomeSaveLives https://t.co/f1PQQrzMIK

To the people who seem to think they‚Äôre invincible: You‚Äôre not. So go home and stay home. You‚Äôre not just putting yourself at risk, you‚Äôre putting others at risk too - nurses and doctors, grocery store workers, your grandparents, and so many others. #StayAtHomeSaveLives

Day in and day out, farmers and food producers across the country continue to work hard so that we have good food in our stores and on our tables. So to them, we say thank you. We know you‚Äôre dealing with the impacts of COVID-19 just like the rest of us, and we‚Äôve got your back.

We have some of the world‚Äôs brightest researchers right here at home, and many of them are stepping up to join the fight against COVID-19. To help them take on this challenge, we‚Äôre announcing direct financial support for vaccine development and production in Canada.

From my family to yours, and to all the kids who‚Äôve had to sacrifice their play dates with friends and didn‚Äôt get the March Break they‚Äôd hoped for, thank you for doing your part. We‚Äôre going to get through this together. https://t.co/u5Trx1rRXq

Whether you‚Äôre a parent worried about paying for rent and groceries, or you‚Äôre a small business owner worried about paying your bills and your staff, know that we‚Äôll do whatever it takes to get you the help you need. That‚Äôs why we‚Äôve asked that the House of Commons be recalled.

full_text: Whether you‚Äôre a Canadian of Irish descent or simply Irish for the day, let‚Äôs celebrate #StPatricksDay a wee bit differently this year... from home. With some social distancing we‚Äôll get through this, and we‚Äôll have another reason to celebrate later, together.

We‚Äôre working closely with public health officials and medical professionals across the country to protect you and your family, but it‚Äôs up to all of us to keep our communities safe. Here are some ways you can help limit the spread of COVID-19. #FlattenTheCurve https://t.co/lFkhnj21oz

This morning, I spoke with G7 leaders about COVID-19. This is a global issue, and we are committed to doing all it takes to protect people & support our economies. We will coordinate our responses & take strong action, together. Read our joint statement: https://t.co/pbfAfLSFYR https://t.co/gLUgEhSrW2

Your health and safety has been - and will always be - our top priority. As the COVID-19 situation continues to evolve, so does our response. Today, we announced significant new measures to keep you, your family, and your community safe. ‚§µÔ∏è https://t.co/dMN3cmXStp

HAPPENING NOW: I‚Äôm speaking from Rideau Cottage about the rapidly evolving COVID-19 outbreak and announcing significant new measures we‚Äôre taking to protect your health and keep you safe. Watch live: https://t.co/ZWtPbeNPVk

This morning, I spoke with the @EU_Commission‚Äôs @vonderleyen about how we can coordinate the international response to COVID-19 to limit its spread, protect people in Canada and European Union countries, and support our economies. More on our call: https://t.co/NwYAAb8Lsp

COVID-19 is a rapidly evolving global challenge, and international coordination is necessary. Ahead of our upcoming call with G7 leaders, I spoke with @eucopresident @CharlesMichel today about the measures being taken in Canada and the EU. Get the details: https://t.co/KdK2s6nAtq

Busy day of meetings and interviews today. COVID-19 is an evolving situation in Canada and around the world, and nothing is off the table as we consider every option to protect the health of Canadians and the economy. More updates to come throughout the day.

Today, I spoke with Premier @francoislegault about the work we‚Äôre doing to protect the health & safety of Quebecers and all Canadians, and the action we‚Äôre taking to support workers & businesses impacted by COVID-19. https://t.co/ZXMfOz1MzP

I spoke on the phone with @POTUS Trump again today. We talked about COVID-19, its impacts, and how we can keep people safe in both our countries - and we‚Äôll continue to stay in touch as the situation evolves. Thanks for the call.

Around the world, the COVID-19 situation continues to evolve rapidly. I want you to know that we‚Äôre working around the clock & doing everything we can to support our economy & keep you safe. And yesterday, we announced additional measures we‚Äôre taking to do just that. ‚§µÔ∏è

Earlier this week, we announced funding that will help Indigenous communities respond to the COVID-19 outbreak - and make sure they have the supplies, equipment, training, and support they need to limit the spread of the virus & address its impacts.

On my call with premiers today, we talked about the COVID-19 outbreak and how we can work together to limit the spread of the virus, minimize its impact on our economy, and keep you safe. Get more details on this morning‚Äôs meeting here ‚§µÔ∏è https://t.co/JDX1VMoP5Z

I got on the phone with @EmmanuelMacron today to talk about coordinating global efforts to address the impacts of COVID-19 - including through the G7. We talked about the steps we‚Äôre taking to protect people‚Äôs health and to limit the impact on economies. https://t.co/N9CD0KF5z2

HAPPENING NOW: I‚Äôm speaking from Rideau Cottage about the COVID-19 outbreak and the steps we‚Äôre taking to address the impacts it‚Äôs having on our economy and keep you safe. Watch live: https://t.co/iGhwO37LWY
Busy day ahead, working from home. Meetings with my cabinet, the country‚Äôs premiers, national Indigenous leaders, and more. Staying focused on you. Talk soon. https://t.co/xhAuxscf6N

I have some additional news to share this evening. Unfortunately, the results of Sophie‚Äôs COVID-19 test are positive. Therefore, she will be in quarantine for the time being. Her symptoms remain mild and she is taking care of herself and following the advice of our doctor.

I spoke with @POTUS Trump today about the work we‚Äôre doing to manage the impacts of COVID-19. Get the details of our conversation here: https://t.co/OohQBrCd1f

COVID-19 is having an impact on the global economy, and today I spoke with @PerrinBeatty and @hassan_yussuff about our pan-Canadian approach to addressing the impacts of the virus and our plan to support businesses & workers who fall on hard times.

I spoke with Prime Minister @GiuseppeConteIT earlier today to talk about the need for international coordination on the response to COVID-19. Italy has been hit particularly hard by the virus, and Canadians stand in solidarity with the Italian people. https://t.co/8LM7hfmJYu

I have some personal news to share today. Sophie recently returned from a speaking event in the UK, and last night she was experiencing mild flu-like symptoms. She‚Äòs feeling better, but following the advice of our doctor she is self-isolating as we wait on COVID-19 test results.

https://t.co/xVr4l9NEyg

Thank you @PattyHajdu for the call tonight

We had a good opportunity to share information and ideas about how to fight COVID-19

Thank you for your work at this difficult time

To get through this crisis, Canadians need:

1) Money in their pocket üí∞
2) A job to go back to üî®
3) A safe place to live üè°

We will keep fighting for you.

Yesterday, I spoke to the Prime Minister about the help Canadians need now, including a $2,000/ month direct income.

Today‚Äôs announcement isn‚Äôt perfect, but it will help so many people. 

We need to work to get it to people as quickly as possible.

We just passed a good first step to help Cdns, incl. things we pushed for:

‚úÖHelp for those left out by EI
‚úÖSuspend student loan payments
‚úÖExtend tax filing deadlines
‚úÖMore $$ for health care
‚úÖEliminate need for Drs‚Äô notes

We‚Äôll keep working to get more help faster for Cdns

As shut-downs become deeper and longer-lasting, we need urgent action to help Canadians make ends meet

We‚Äôre calling on the government to move quickly on 8 measures to help people now:

1. Immediate assistance to all Canadians - $2,000 per adult and $250 per child

This loss would be devastating

We need to act today to save these jobs and make sure our workers continue to get paid

The government should follow the lead of other countries and implement a wage subsidy of more than 75% now to protect people‚Äôs jobs

https://t.co/6vkwf8SevF

People are struggling with the impact of COVID-19

New Democrats are suggesting two solutions to help right away:

1. Direct Assistance
2. Freeze on Firing https://t.co/kTQH82SNrm

MPs came back to Ottawa to pass what‚Äôs needed to help Canadians. 
Let‚Äôs do that. 
The Liberals should drop what we don‚Äôt agree on and focus on what we were sent here to do - deliver for Canadians.

Today we are calling for immediate help for all Canadians:

1) IMMEDIATE DIRECT HELP: Sending $2,000 with an additional $250 per child directly to all Canadians (Universal Basic Income)

2) FIRING FREEZE: Giving employers more than 75% in a wage subsidy to keep people employed
This is what we need to do right now, people need help and can't afford to wait https://t.co/W1ZxPv8y9h

Everyone should get paid sick leave.

Everyone who loses a job should get employment insurance,

Not just now, but always

https://t.co/OqfuGCw08d

Canadians cannot wait a moment longer for help

Today I wrote to the PM committing New Democrats will provide the necessary votes to pass measures to help people

It is my hope that our support will get the ball rolling on these measures so that Canadians get help right away https://t.co/zJgSiQrBbu

The battle ahead is tough, but Jack is tougher

Sending love and strength to you my friend and to your family & friends

We‚Äôre here for you https://t.co/CRgpZXzpZB

full_text:
Friends, I am at home today, feeling unwell.

I have been in contact with a doctor and they do not believe I have symptoms consistent with COVID19. But their advice is for me to limit contact with the public until I am feeling better.

The majority of workers - 60% - won‚Äôt be helped by today‚Äôs Liberal announcement on COVID19.

Other countries have found a way to give people paid sick leave so they can stay home.

Canada must do better.

This morning my friend Ed Broadbent joined us to share some of his wisdom.

I always tell Ed, I want to be like him when I grow up. 

He is a kind mentor, generous with his time. 

Despite retiring from politics, he continues to find ways to build a brighter future for people. https://t.co/3SpKD1aUyb

It‚Äôs been 44 days since the first case of COVID19 in Canada. 

And still no help for those who don‚Äôt have sick leave and can‚Äôt stay home. 

And today the Liberal Minister of Labour says she hasn‚Äôt heard any concerns from workers. 

What will it take to get the Liberals to act?

And still!

Burnaby South Rebels bring home a second championship back to back!

I want to congratulate the players & coaches @RebelsAthletics and the school @bbysouthSD41 supporters & fans!

https://t.co/Fp0Eszfe57

Canadians need help now. 

Governments need to invest to create good jobs and protect the services we all count on, like health care.

This year‚Äôs theme for International Women‚Äôs Day is #EachforEqual. As we celebrate women & how far we've come it's also a time to reflect on how much further we need to go

It‚Äôs not enough for Mr. Trudeau to say he's a feminist if he doesn‚Äôt back it up with real action 1/2

Canadians pay some of the highest prices for cell phones and internet in the world

Yet, Liberals continue to give millions in handouts to big companies like Bell, Rogers and Telus who make billions in profit 

1/2

How can a worker stay home if they dont have sick leave? How will they pay their bills?

In the face of coronavirus, the Liberal government needs a plan to help workers. https://t.co/ITn5JdNRLT

When the premiers want to meet, it takes Justin Trudeau 1 day. When big corporations want to meet, he finds time. 

But when the Wet'suwet'en hereditary chiefs ask to meet for weeks, they're ignored.

The PM's failure of leadership has allowed this to become a national crisis. https://t.co/mplfwUug3F

I got to join hundreds of members of @CanadianLabour last night to talk about our shared vision for universal, comprehensive pharmacare that covers everyone ‚Äì and the plan New Democrats have laid out to deliver medication coverage for Canadians. https://t.co/tpdak5bXrP

We‚Äôre fighting to deliver what people need.

üîòPharmacare & Dentacare

So I just had a meeting with Prime Minister Trudeau. Here's where things are at üîä #cdnpoli https://t.co/h3Djgb33wC

Tomorrow I'm meeting with PM @JustinTrudeau.

On the shortlist for me:

1. Work together to deliver universal pharmacare for all.

2. Stop taking Indigenous kids to court & drop the appeal of the ruling on First Nations child welfare.

And more ‚Äì looking forward to it. #cdnpoli

Don, let me introduce you to ‚Äú#youpeople‚Äù

My great grandfather, Hira Singh, who served in WW1 & WW2 under the British.

We honour all who served. #RemembranceSunday https://t.co/pNeBlJMC4R

22 years. 

That's how long the Liberals have been promising Pharmacare while Canadians wait.

Now is the time @Justintrudeau.

Work with us & let's deliver universal medication coverage for every single Canadian.
¬†
We can do this for people. #cdnpoli https://t.co/XQ536ZxTPp

This is Canada's chance.

This is what we've been saying all along.

US Democrats want stronger and enforceable labour and environmental protections in the #USMCA.

Mr. Trudeau, take the opportunity, and do the work that's needed to deliver the same for Canadians. #cdnpoli https://t.co/DAxzdTNVEO

I'm in this for working people.

For moms & dads caring for their kids & ageing parents.
